Show HN: Chroma – One copy of Electron to rule them all
text:
chroma keeps a central, up-to-date version of Electron, and makes all your installed Electron apps use it, in order to save disk space.

Current caveats: linux only, no flatpak or AppImage support. Currently trying ot figure out how to integrate with Flatpak nicely.

Ask HN: How do you feel about AI-generated writing?
text:
I wanted to get your perspective on AI-generated writing. If I were to come across a blog post here that I found interesting but later discovered that it was generated by AI, I would feel a bit off about it.

However, if the post contained all the valid and relevant points, does it really matter if it was written by a machine or a human? Is the authenticity of human writing always necessary, or can AI-generated content be just as valuable?

I'm curious to hear your opinions on this matter.
